I think they need someone like Dean Henderson so that they can have some level of confidence if they loose the ball in the box. He's proven his worth at Sheffield and could be a target for a much better club in the next transfer window, and I think he could suit the irons nicely. With an injured Fabianski and a loaned out Roberto (even though hes not that good), they've screwed themselves and are worried at all times when the ball's in their defensive third, even against weaker teams, probably even some championship teams to be fair aswell.
